      "writtenOn": "2026-06-02T18:55:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I think there are some repos which are important but not actively developed in which it makes sense to allow a maintainer to remain, assuming they are responsive to any changes, even if they are not actively committing to OpenBMC anymore. \n\nI would suggest that we should still mark them not as an active maintainer.  If someone is only focused on that one repository that was developed years ago, and not actively engaging with new changes or elsewhere in the project, how do they satisfy this?\n\n```\n* Work with other subproject owners to maintain the project\u0027s overall health and success holistically.\n* Keep abreast of technical changes to the overall project and maintain and/or delegate maintenance of the subproject to keep it aligned with the overall project.\n```",
